1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:42,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:50,154 --> 00:00:51,239
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

3
00:00:51,322 --> 00:00:52,574
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

4
00:00:52,657 --> 00:00:54,075
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:55,076
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

6
00:01:01,374 --> 00:01:02,876
Where's patient Shin I-rang?

7
00:01:02,959 --> 00:01:04,502
Are you Mr. Shin I-rang's guardian?

8
00:01:04,586 --> 00:01:05,587
Yes.

9
00:01:05,670 --> 00:01:07,255
I'm sorry.

10
00:01:07,338 --> 00:01:10,300
He was already unconscious
when he arrived at the hospital.

11
00:01:23,438 --> 00:01:24,606
No.

12
00:01:34,073 --> 00:01:35,450
I should've been there.

13
00:01:39,162 --> 00:01:41,748
I should've been with him.

14
00:02:30,922 --> 00:02:31,881
What…

15
00:02:33,132 --> 00:02:34,384
Am I…

16
00:02:35,093 --> 00:02:36,594
Am I dead?

17
00:02:43,017 --> 00:02:44,018
Am I…

18
00:02:46,104 --> 00:02:48,106
dead for real?

19
00:02:51,234 --> 00:02:52,527
Mister.

20
00:02:55,321 --> 00:02:56,698
Who are you?

21
00:02:57,865 --> 00:02:58,783
Wait.

22
00:02:59,951 --> 00:03:01,285
Who am I?

23
00:03:01,828 --> 00:03:02,954
Mister.

24
00:03:04,622 --> 00:03:06,082
You have to go there.

25
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:11,421
Where is there?

26
00:03:16,259 --> 00:03:17,760
Mother, he's here!

27
00:03:27,812 --> 00:03:31,065
I-rang.

28
00:03:31,149 --> 00:03:33,109
I-rang, Mom is here.

29
00:03:34,027 --> 00:03:37,071
Doctor, what happened to my son?

30
00:03:54,297 --> 00:03:55,923
Don't go out there.

31
00:03:58,885 --> 00:04:01,512
Mister, don't go.

32
00:04:04,140 --> 00:04:06,142
What happened to my son, doctor?

33
00:04:07,060 --> 00:04:09,729
Please. Please help him, doctor.

34
00:04:09,812 --> 00:04:12,607
We've already tried CPR several times.

35
00:04:12,690 --> 00:04:15,401
-Doctor.
-Please. I beg you.

36
00:04:17,403 --> 00:04:18,946
You said…

37
00:04:20,865 --> 00:04:22,700
you'd find my mom for me.

38
00:04:32,251 --> 00:04:37,131
Patient Shin I-rang is pronounced dead
at 8:43 p.m. on August 16…

39
00:04:38,132 --> 00:04:40,593
What… Did you hear that?

40
00:04:40,676 --> 00:04:42,512
-Get the defibrillator.
-Yes, doctor.

41
00:04:42,595 --> 00:04:44,597
-What's going on…
-Please move aside.

42
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:47,100
-No.
-Folks, please move back.

43
00:04:47,183 --> 00:04:48,726
-But…
-Come this way.

44
00:04:48,810 --> 00:04:49,977
I-rang.

45
00:04:50,478 --> 00:04:51,479
Clear!

46
00:04:52,897 --> 00:04:54,023
Charge to 200 joules.

47
00:05:06,619 --> 00:05:08,079
EKG has returned!

48
00:05:14,419 --> 00:05:16,921
-I-rang, can you see me?
-I-rang.

49
00:05:17,588 --> 00:05:19,090
I-rang, can you hear me?

50
00:05:26,264 --> 00:05:27,598
Attorney Shin…

51
00:05:47,410 --> 00:05:48,536
…Reporter Park Seong-chan.

52
00:05:49,453 --> 00:05:53,583
We will bring you more updates on Cho
as the story develops.

53
00:05:53,666 --> 00:05:57,962
Next, let's meet the hero
who saved the kidnapped child, Kwon.

54
00:05:58,045 --> 00:05:59,881
-Reporter Kim Bo-ra?
-There it comes.

55
00:05:59,964 --> 00:06:02,925
I'm currently at the hospital
where Mr. Shin I-rang is hospitalized.

56
00:06:03,009 --> 00:06:06,262
Mr. Shin got shot in the process
of saving the child,

57
00:06:06,345 --> 00:06:08,472
-but he's undergoing a smooth recovery--
-He's coming out.

58
00:06:09,015 --> 00:06:11,601
-Mr. Shin is coming out now.
-Mr. Shin!

59
00:06:20,943 --> 00:06:22,153
A word, please!

60
00:06:27,241 --> 00:06:30,244
Lightning…

61
00:06:46,552 --> 00:06:48,679
Lightning…

62
00:06:55,561 --> 00:06:57,855
Uncle.

63
00:06:57,939 --> 00:07:00,524
You're so cool. You're the best!

64
00:07:02,652 --> 00:07:03,486
You think?

65
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:07,907
If you say so, I guess I really am cool.

66
00:07:08,574 --> 00:07:09,700
What a relief.

67
00:07:10,409 --> 00:07:11,536
-Ouch!
-Oh, no.

68
00:07:11,619 --> 00:07:13,621
-Are you okay?
-Careful.

69
00:07:17,416 --> 00:07:19,460
-That fool.
-Get some rest, okay?

70
00:07:20,378 --> 00:07:22,338
-Thanks, everyone.
-See you later.

71
00:07:22,922 --> 00:07:24,757
Bong-su, power!

72
00:07:25,424 --> 00:07:27,134
I-rang, power!

73
00:07:29,345 --> 00:07:32,473
-Let's go.
-Gosh, you've been through a lot.

74
00:07:32,557 --> 00:07:34,433
Have some time alone. We'll be back soon.

75
00:07:41,107 --> 00:07:42,483
Attorney Han cried?

76
00:07:42,567 --> 00:07:47,238
She cried her eyes out,
saying she should've been with you.

77
00:07:48,155 --> 00:07:49,699
She did?

78
00:07:53,077 --> 00:07:54,704
She cried her eyes out?

79
00:08:00,418 --> 00:08:01,877
What's so funny?

80
00:08:01,961 --> 00:08:03,754
Oh, Attorney Han.

81
00:08:06,382 --> 00:08:07,466
Are you okay?

82
00:08:08,050 --> 00:08:10,261
Why can't you be more careful?
You got shot.

83
00:08:11,762 --> 00:08:13,139
I'm okay. I mean it.

84
00:08:18,185 --> 00:08:20,646
Mister, can I go to your house?

85
00:08:21,689 --> 00:08:25,860
Do that. It must be boring to stay here.
Go have fun with Da-bong and her grandma.

86
00:08:26,694 --> 00:08:27,778
Okay!

87
00:08:28,279 --> 00:08:29,947
Yay!

88
00:08:34,118 --> 00:08:35,786
Si-ho left.

89
00:08:43,419 --> 00:08:46,005
You must've been shocked because of me.

90
00:08:47,506 --> 00:08:49,592
I was shocked and upset.

91
00:08:52,094 --> 00:08:55,681
You should've gone with Bong-su or me
to handle such a thing.

92
00:08:55,765 --> 00:08:57,516
It was dangerous to go there alone.

93
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,268
You're right.

94
00:09:00,144 --> 00:09:02,104
I guess I was in a rush.

95
00:09:03,022 --> 00:09:07,026
I wanted to find out who Si-ho was
as soon as possible.

96
00:09:10,196 --> 00:09:11,280
Oh, right.

97
00:09:12,239 --> 00:09:14,825
The day you went to find Si-ho,

98
00:09:14,909 --> 00:09:18,162
his dad visited the office
for a divorce consultation.

99
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,498
Divorce?

100
00:09:20,581 --> 00:09:22,541
They've been living apart
since Si-ho went missing.

101
00:09:23,417 --> 00:09:27,338
Both of them are struggling with regret
and a sense of guilt.

102
00:09:28,130 --> 00:09:31,759
They don't even know if he's alive.
I bet it's worse for them.

103
00:09:32,343 --> 00:09:33,344
You're right.

104
00:09:34,679 --> 00:09:36,180
A slim chance

105
00:09:37,098 --> 00:09:38,808
can cause more pain sometimes.

106
00:09:41,977 --> 00:09:45,064
Anyway, how's the investigation going?

107
00:09:45,815 --> 00:09:47,858
It's taking place under detention

108
00:09:47,942 --> 00:09:50,027
thanks to Ye-jun
who was rescued from the scene.

109
00:09:50,945 --> 00:09:54,281
But Cho Chi-yeong is pleading the Fifth
regarding Si-ho

110
00:09:54,365 --> 00:09:56,158
who went missing more than a year ago.

111
00:09:57,326 --> 00:09:59,537
Ye-jun and Si-ho are around the same age

112
00:09:59,620 --> 00:10:03,332
and were both in yellow rain boots.

113
00:10:04,125 --> 00:10:07,169
Nevertheless, no evidence proves
that he kidnapped Si-ho.

114
00:10:11,090 --> 00:10:12,091
What are you doing?

115
00:10:12,842 --> 00:10:15,511
A sentence for abduction, enticement,
and confinement of a minor

116
00:10:15,594 --> 00:10:17,555
is only a max sentence
of ten years in prison.

117
00:10:17,638 --> 00:10:19,765
It'll be a much lighter sentence
in reality.

118
00:10:20,433 --> 00:10:21,726
I can't let that happen.

119
00:10:24,228 --> 00:10:25,521
I'll help you like this.

120
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:29,358
-Oh, gosh.
-I-rang was shot!

121
00:10:29,442 --> 00:10:30,443
Sorry. My bad.

122
00:10:31,652 --> 00:10:32,862
At least, let's walk in step.

123
00:10:32,945 --> 00:10:34,447
Left foot, left foot.

124
00:10:34,530 --> 00:10:36,741
What for? We're not soldiers.

125
00:10:37,366 --> 00:10:38,200
Oops!

126
00:10:38,284 --> 00:10:39,201
Oh, come on!

127
00:10:40,161 --> 00:10:42,037
Are you okay?

128
00:10:46,959 --> 00:10:48,544
"I slept like a baby."

129
00:10:48,627 --> 00:10:50,588
"Did you sleep well?"

130
00:10:50,671 --> 00:10:52,423
I wish I could play too.

131
00:10:53,048 --> 00:10:54,550
"Honey, did you have a good night?"

132
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:55,593
"Of course."

133
00:10:57,428 --> 00:10:59,263
"We should have breakfast."

134
00:10:59,346 --> 00:11:01,640
"Let's have breakfast and…"

135
00:11:01,724 --> 00:11:04,518
"Honey, do you have an acting gig today?"

136
00:11:05,478 --> 00:11:08,230
"Yes, I play a doctor role today."

137
00:11:08,314 --> 00:11:10,858
"My gosh, that's amazing."

138
00:11:11,942 --> 00:11:14,487
Dad, can you not go to work?

139
00:11:15,196 --> 00:11:17,031
I want to spend time with you.

140
00:11:17,615 --> 00:11:20,117
"Should we go to the amusement park
with Da-bong this weekend?"

141
00:11:20,701 --> 00:11:23,746
"Nice idea. That's my wife, Sa-rang."

142
00:11:24,497 --> 00:11:26,081
I want to go camping.

143
00:11:26,165 --> 00:11:27,791
"Good luck with the shoot."

144
00:11:27,875 --> 00:11:29,752
"Okay, thanks."

145
00:11:38,636 --> 00:11:40,804
Excuse me.

146
00:11:40,888 --> 00:11:42,973
I'm here about the boy named Yoon Si-ho.

147
00:11:45,267 --> 00:11:47,478
Are you Si-ho's father?

148
00:11:49,271 --> 00:11:50,856
Do you know my son?

149
00:11:51,899 --> 00:11:53,317
I heard from the police.

150
00:11:54,276 --> 00:11:55,986
That he went missing a year ago.

151
00:12:00,449 --> 00:12:02,451
You saved the boy named Ye-jun.

152
00:12:03,619 --> 00:12:04,620
Do you

153
00:12:05,454 --> 00:12:08,999
happen to know where Si-ho is?

154
00:12:11,252 --> 00:12:12,253
No.

155
00:12:13,337 --> 00:12:14,547
I'm sorry.

156
00:12:17,841 --> 00:12:19,134
I see.

157
00:12:38,529 --> 00:12:39,488
Hello?

158
00:12:42,783 --> 00:12:43,909
He doesn't know.

159
00:12:46,412 --> 00:12:48,956
Honey? Are you okay?

160
00:12:50,082 --> 00:12:51,500
Do you want me to go there now?

161
00:12:55,129 --> 00:12:57,298
Okay, I'm sorry. I just…

162
00:12:58,799 --> 00:13:00,759
Our Si-ho will be okay.

163
00:13:01,468 --> 00:13:04,471
Let's wait a little more, okay?

164
00:13:11,103 --> 00:13:13,939
He said he'd let you in the police car?

165
00:13:15,274 --> 00:13:16,442
Yes.

166
00:13:17,109 --> 00:13:20,446
He was a stranger.
Weren't you scared of him?

167
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:22,615
He wasn't a stranger.

168
00:13:23,157 --> 00:13:27,286
That detective gave
a safety lesson at school.

169
00:13:29,663 --> 00:13:32,875
In that case,
it must've been easier to trust him.

170
00:13:32,958 --> 00:13:36,170
And he was really good to me.

171
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:40,174
He showed me his pistol
and played with me.

172
00:13:42,343 --> 00:13:46,764
But when I wanted to go home at night,

173
00:13:47,681 --> 00:13:51,727
he stopped me, saying he'd take me
somewhere fun the next day.

174
00:13:53,187 --> 00:13:57,107
I still said I was going to go home,

175
00:13:57,191 --> 00:13:58,651
and he got angry.

176
00:14:00,778 --> 00:14:02,112
The truth is,

177
00:14:02,780 --> 00:14:05,658
I had a headache since that morning.

178
00:14:07,618 --> 00:14:11,872
It got worse as he yelled at me.

179
00:14:13,749 --> 00:14:16,669
Did it hurt badly?

180
00:14:17,836 --> 00:14:18,837
Yes.

181
00:14:20,673 --> 00:14:22,007
So,

182
00:14:23,050 --> 00:14:25,177
I took medicine and kept sleeping.

183
00:14:25,886 --> 00:14:28,055
When I opened my eyes,

184
00:14:28,138 --> 00:14:30,099
I was in your office.

185
00:14:33,435 --> 00:14:34,395
I see.

186
00:14:39,608 --> 00:14:42,111
I miss my parents.

187
00:14:43,487 --> 00:14:45,114
Can't I go see them?

188
00:14:50,327 --> 00:14:51,161
Si-ho.

189
00:14:52,621 --> 00:14:55,874
I'm afraid you can't see your mom and dad

190
00:14:56,542 --> 00:14:57,626
right now.

191
00:14:58,877 --> 00:14:59,920
Why?

192
00:15:01,338 --> 00:15:02,548
Your parents are…

193
00:15:04,758 --> 00:15:06,510
a little sick.

194
00:15:07,636 --> 00:15:10,097
Really? How sick are they?

195
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:13,225
They're heartsick.

196
00:15:14,768 --> 00:15:15,728
Why?

197
00:15:17,646 --> 00:15:18,856
Let's say

198
00:15:20,232 --> 00:15:23,068
your friend tripped next to you.

199
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:25,738
How would you feel?

200
00:15:29,575 --> 00:15:31,118
I'd feel sorry

201
00:15:32,161 --> 00:15:33,704
for not stopping him from tripping.

202
00:15:34,872 --> 00:15:35,748
Right.

203
00:15:37,374 --> 00:15:41,587
You'd feel sorry
even if it weren't your fault.

204
00:15:42,546 --> 00:15:45,215
Your parents are feeling the same way.

205
00:15:48,635 --> 00:15:50,596
They couldn't protect you,

206
00:15:51,930 --> 00:15:53,807
their precious son.

207
00:15:55,642 --> 00:15:59,563
Thinking of what they could've done,

208
00:16:01,273 --> 00:16:03,025
they constantly blame themselves.

209
00:16:05,569 --> 00:16:06,528
That's why

210
00:16:07,654 --> 00:16:10,074
it makes them more and more heartsick.

211
00:16:10,783 --> 00:16:12,618
That's not good.

212
00:16:14,286 --> 00:16:17,664
How do you treat being heartsick?

213
00:16:18,499 --> 00:16:22,878
I want my mom and dad to be happy again.

214
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:30,385
If they know that you're this okay,

215
00:16:31,178 --> 00:16:32,763
it might ease their pain a little.

216
00:16:35,390 --> 00:16:37,893
But they don't know.

217
00:16:39,436 --> 00:16:41,271
They can't see

218
00:16:42,022 --> 00:16:43,774
or hear me.

219
00:16:44,358 --> 00:16:45,734
Don't worry.

220
00:16:45,818 --> 00:16:47,444
I'll help you.

221
00:16:49,530 --> 00:16:50,489
Okay.

222
00:16:52,241 --> 00:16:53,158
Then…

223
00:17:03,210 --> 00:17:04,086
Whoosh.

224
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:06,171
Whoosh.

225
00:17:16,557 --> 00:17:17,683
Let's go.

226
00:17:17,766 --> 00:17:18,892
Give me your briefcase.

227
00:17:23,230 --> 00:17:24,064
Wait.

228
00:17:24,148 --> 00:17:26,150
Oh, my! I'm sorry.

229
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:29,027
-Knock it off!
-Okay, my bad.

230
00:17:37,077 --> 00:17:38,620
Hello. You came early.

231
00:17:39,204 --> 00:17:42,249
-How are you feeling?
-I'm okay. Let's get started.

232
00:17:44,835 --> 00:17:47,254
Cho Chi-yeong divorced his wife
after she had an affair

233
00:17:47,337 --> 00:17:49,131
and raised his son, Gyeong-seo, alone.

234
00:17:49,214 --> 00:17:51,842
Two years ago
while Cho went to the bathroom,

235
00:17:51,925 --> 00:17:55,804
his unattended son climbed on a desk, fell
through a torn window screen, and died.

236
00:17:56,972 --> 00:18:00,851
His ex-wife reported him
for child neglect,

237
00:18:00,934 --> 00:18:06,106
but the court ruled that he didn't neglect
his parental duties despite his busy work.

238
00:18:06,690 --> 00:18:10,611
I don't see anything unusual so far.

239
00:18:11,361 --> 00:18:16,450
I wonder why he kidnapped children
and murdered one after losing his own son.

240
00:18:20,996 --> 00:18:22,039
We're back to square one.

241
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:25,834
What do we have about the case?

242
00:18:26,376 --> 00:18:30,255
The police took these photos at the scene
when his son fell to his death.

243
00:18:35,761 --> 00:18:38,805
His son must've loved pizza.

244
00:18:38,889 --> 00:18:41,934
He diligently collected coupons
and even drew some.

245
00:18:42,017 --> 00:18:44,519
He drew fake coupons?

246
00:18:44,603 --> 00:18:48,523
It could be more like
he wanted to win a prize.

247
00:18:48,607 --> 00:18:50,234
What were the prizes?

248
00:18:51,026 --> 00:18:52,778
-That's it!
-What?

249
00:18:54,446 --> 00:18:58,033
A six-year-old boy collected coupons
over a kimchi refrigerator?

250
00:18:59,034 --> 00:19:00,202
No way.

251
00:19:00,285 --> 00:19:02,120
Hold on. Let's see. When was it?

252
00:19:02,204 --> 00:19:03,247
Three or so years ago,

253
00:19:03,330 --> 00:19:06,500
a neighborhood supermarket hosted a prize
festival to celebrate their grand opening.

254
00:19:07,501 --> 00:19:11,838
Da-bong won a television, the first prize.

255
00:19:12,339 --> 00:19:14,424
But she cried.

256
00:19:15,133 --> 00:19:15,968
Why?

257
00:19:16,051 --> 00:19:20,305
Because she wanted the fifth prize,
a cartoon-character backpack.

258
00:19:21,807 --> 00:19:24,851
How children think is totally different
from how adults think.

259
00:19:26,144 --> 00:19:29,481
Then, from a child's perspective…

260
00:19:31,858 --> 00:19:32,776
What about this one?

261
00:19:34,069 --> 00:19:34,987
I think that's it.

262
00:19:35,570 --> 00:19:37,906
Children love camping.

263
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:41,702
I want to go camping.

264
00:19:41,785 --> 00:19:45,956
He stopped me, saying he'd take me
somewhere fun the next day.

265
00:19:46,039 --> 00:19:49,751
Cho Chi-yeong told Si-ho
that they'd go somewhere fun the next day.

266
00:19:49,835 --> 00:19:51,837
It may have been a camping site.

267
00:19:52,587 --> 00:19:56,466
Si-ho said that Cho Chi-yeong
gave a safety lesson at school.

268
00:19:56,550 --> 00:20:01,555
What if he was seeking a target
at the time?

269
00:20:02,180 --> 00:20:05,267
And what if he wanted
to give himself a chance?

270
00:20:07,185 --> 00:20:09,438
To himself who couldn't protect his son?

271
00:20:09,521 --> 00:20:13,275
In fact, he called Ye-jun his son.

272
00:20:13,358 --> 00:20:16,236
And he fed Ye-jun pizza,
which was his son's favorite.

273
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:18,030
So, in short,

274
00:20:18,113 --> 00:20:19,656
he didn't look for a target of revenge,

275
00:20:19,740 --> 00:20:22,909
but a chance for himself to be a good dad?

276
00:20:22,993 --> 00:20:24,661
He's a total lunatic.

277
00:20:24,745 --> 00:20:27,414
If he was going to take Si-ho

278
00:20:27,497 --> 00:20:29,708
to the camping site
his son wanted to go to,

279
00:20:29,791 --> 00:20:32,669
he may have buried Si-ho there.

280
00:20:33,253 --> 00:20:35,005
It's plausible, but it's a little…

281
00:20:35,088 --> 00:20:36,256
Uncertain. I know.

282
00:20:36,798 --> 00:20:38,800
So, I'm going to ask him in person.

283
00:20:39,885 --> 00:20:41,887
I doubt he'll agree to meet you.

284
00:20:41,970 --> 00:20:43,347
He won't talk to me,

285
00:20:44,723 --> 00:20:47,309
but he'll talk to Si-ho.

286
00:20:56,902 --> 00:20:59,821
CHO CHI-YEONG

287
00:20:59,905 --> 00:21:01,656
TO: SEOUL CORRECTIONAL FACILITY

288
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:03,533
FROM: SECOND FLOOR OF
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

289
00:21:20,050 --> 00:21:21,885
To Mr. Detective.

290
00:21:22,636 --> 00:21:25,305
Mister, this is Si-ho.

291
00:21:25,972 --> 00:21:28,975
The Yoon Si-ho that you said
had a nice, round head.

292
00:21:29,976 --> 00:21:33,897
We played word chain
and cops and robbers together.

293
00:21:34,564 --> 00:21:37,692
You showed me your pistol too.

294
00:21:37,776 --> 00:21:38,985
Do you remember?

295
00:21:41,488 --> 00:21:44,032
Cho Chi-yeong may stay silent
until the end.

296
00:21:44,116 --> 00:21:47,285
Can you look for Si-ho's body
at the camping site with Bong-su?

297
00:21:47,869 --> 00:21:48,787
Okay.

298
00:21:56,044 --> 00:22:01,883
GOOD SLEEPING CAMPING SITE

299
00:22:03,844 --> 00:22:08,014
We have only one person from the police?

300
00:22:08,098 --> 00:22:10,267
I barely got my day off to come here too.

301
00:22:10,851 --> 00:22:12,436
We still lack evidence.

302
00:22:13,562 --> 00:22:17,399
Even so, why can't they
just believe what the hero says?

303
00:22:17,482 --> 00:22:18,650
My point exactly.

304
00:22:20,652 --> 00:22:22,654
This place is so big.
Will we be able to find him?

305
00:22:23,405 --> 00:22:24,364
We must.

306
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:27,284
Everything is possible with God.

307
00:22:27,367 --> 00:22:28,702
There are just four of us,

308
00:22:29,286 --> 00:22:32,747
but he will give us the ability
of 40 or even 400.

309
00:22:37,085 --> 00:22:39,296
Let me give you some precautions first.

310
00:22:40,088 --> 00:22:43,383
Plant growth is different
at the burial site due to organic matter.

311
00:22:43,466 --> 00:22:47,470
So pay attention to areas
with uneven growth or unusual coloring.

312
00:22:47,554 --> 00:22:50,932
And I sent each of you
a metal-detecting app.

313
00:22:51,016 --> 00:22:52,642
Hold your phones close to the ground

314
00:22:52,726 --> 00:22:56,730
and they react to things
like buttons, keys, or zippers.

315
00:22:58,815 --> 00:23:01,067
Attorney Han and Father,

316
00:23:01,776 --> 00:23:03,361
please search that side.

317
00:23:03,445 --> 00:23:05,739
You and I will search this side.

318
00:23:05,822 --> 00:23:06,823
Okay.

319
00:23:07,782 --> 00:23:09,367
Are you a police officer?

320
00:23:16,333 --> 00:23:17,459
Shall we?

321
00:23:19,085 --> 00:23:20,212
I'll do my best.

322
00:23:37,229 --> 00:23:38,438
It's you again.

323
00:23:40,857 --> 00:23:42,150
Who are you, really?

324
00:23:46,321 --> 00:23:47,572
Who are you

325
00:23:48,448 --> 00:23:50,367
to send me such a letter?

326
00:23:55,872 --> 00:23:57,249
Si-ho is…

327
00:23:59,251 --> 00:24:00,502
here right now.

328
00:24:04,256 --> 00:24:05,382
What are you saying?

329
00:24:05,465 --> 00:24:09,344
Otherwise, how else would I know
what happened between you and him?

330
00:24:12,138 --> 00:24:13,390
Stop lying.

331
00:24:14,933 --> 00:24:16,351
Stop messing around.

332
00:24:16,434 --> 00:24:18,853
You kidnapped Ye-jun and Si-ho.

333
00:24:20,355 --> 00:24:21,940
And you caused Si-ho to die.

334
00:24:23,358 --> 00:24:26,361
Anyone can see
you're a despicable criminal.

335
00:24:26,444 --> 00:24:28,029
But I think…

336
00:24:30,657 --> 00:24:31,950
you as Gyeong-seo's dad…

337
00:24:34,202 --> 00:24:36,705
would be a little different.

338
00:24:45,964 --> 00:24:49,301
Please, Gyeong-seo's father.

339
00:24:50,176 --> 00:24:52,262
Think of Si-ho's parents.

340
00:24:53,096 --> 00:24:55,390
Unable to find their beloved son's body,

341
00:24:56,599 --> 00:24:58,935
they're living in utter despair.

342
00:25:01,438 --> 00:25:03,273
You know how it feels to lose a child.

343
00:25:03,356 --> 00:25:04,524
Shut your trap.

344
00:25:06,568 --> 00:25:08,111
You must've wanted to be forgiven.

345
00:25:09,529 --> 00:25:11,114
After Gyeong-seo died,

346
00:25:12,407 --> 00:25:14,367
you must've had so many regrets.

347
00:25:15,493 --> 00:25:19,331
So you tried to prove that you weren't
a bad dad and ease your guilt

348
00:25:19,414 --> 00:25:22,917
by doing what you couldn't do
to your son with those children.

349
00:25:23,001 --> 00:25:26,046
-Shut up!
-For such an absurd reason,

350
00:25:26,129 --> 00:25:29,341
you gave Ye-jun an unforgettable trauma,
let Si-ho die,

351
00:25:30,592 --> 00:25:31,885
and devastated their parents.

352
00:25:31,968 --> 00:25:33,511
What do you know?

353
00:25:36,598 --> 00:25:37,682
I know…

354
00:25:40,352 --> 00:25:41,936
that parents mean the world…

355
00:25:43,730 --> 00:25:45,273
to their children.

356
00:25:50,445 --> 00:25:53,573
You robbed those children of everything.

357
00:26:13,009 --> 00:26:14,427
I don't know who Si-ho is.

358
00:26:16,429 --> 00:26:20,308
And if his parents really loved him,

359
00:26:22,727 --> 00:26:24,687
they wouldn't have left him alone.

360
00:26:26,147 --> 00:26:27,607
Such parents…

361
00:26:29,234 --> 00:26:30,944
don't deserve to be parents.

362
00:26:38,118 --> 00:26:40,703
Don't say that about my mom and dad.

363
00:26:42,622 --> 00:26:45,041
My parents

364
00:26:45,125 --> 00:26:46,793
loved me.

365
00:26:47,460 --> 00:26:49,421
They did everything for me.

366
00:26:50,922 --> 00:26:53,007
To buy me delicious food,

367
00:26:53,633 --> 00:26:55,718
my mom saved on buying make up.

368
00:26:56,678 --> 00:26:59,556
My dad worked until late at night

369
00:27:00,265 --> 00:27:02,350
to buy me a pair of cute rain boots.

370
00:27:03,518 --> 00:27:07,355
They're the one and only parents I have.

371
00:27:08,606 --> 00:27:10,817
I love them so much.

372
00:27:12,152 --> 00:27:16,072
I wouldn't trade them
for a hundred pizzas.

373
00:27:16,156 --> 00:27:20,702
I wouldn't trade them
even for an amusement park.

374
00:27:26,249 --> 00:27:27,959
Mister…

375
00:27:29,502 --> 00:27:31,880
why are you trying to trade him?

376
00:27:35,258 --> 00:27:37,552
I'm not your son.

377
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:45,393
He must've loved you so much too.

378
00:27:49,689 --> 00:27:52,233
If I were your son,

379
00:27:53,151 --> 00:27:55,069
I'd be sad.

380
00:28:00,575 --> 00:28:02,035
Mister.

381
00:28:03,495 --> 00:28:04,996
Why are you crying?

382
00:28:07,874 --> 00:28:08,833
I…

383
00:28:11,294 --> 00:28:13,546
I wanted to do my best for Gyeong-seo.

384
00:28:16,466 --> 00:28:18,676
It felt like my fault
that he was separated from his mom

385
00:28:20,553 --> 00:28:22,764
and that he was left alone.

386
00:28:27,227 --> 00:28:28,561
If I had another chance…

387
00:28:29,812 --> 00:28:32,607
I thought I'd do better
if I had another chance.

388
00:28:43,034 --> 00:28:45,078
I didn't know you were that sick.

389
00:28:46,287 --> 00:28:47,914
I thought you simply had a fever.

390
00:28:49,207 --> 00:28:51,167
You were dead
when I came back the next morning.

391
00:28:52,377 --> 00:28:54,379
I was utterly shocked.

392
00:28:58,550 --> 00:28:59,676
I'm sorry.

393
00:29:02,512 --> 00:29:04,389
I'm truly sorry.

394
00:29:05,139 --> 00:29:06,057
Truly.

395
00:29:07,809 --> 00:29:09,811
If you're truly sorry,

396
00:29:11,521 --> 00:29:13,773
bring me back to my parents.

397
00:29:16,943 --> 00:29:19,904
Where am I right now?

398
00:29:36,963 --> 00:29:38,214
-Check here.
-Yes, sir.

399
00:29:38,298 --> 00:29:39,716
On the right.

400
00:29:53,187 --> 00:29:54,147
What?

401
00:30:06,284 --> 00:30:07,911
Si-ho…

402
00:30:15,376 --> 00:30:16,586
Are you sure about this?

403
00:30:18,838 --> 00:30:21,966
They both said they were ready.

404
00:30:24,218 --> 00:30:25,720
What about Si-ho, though?

405
00:30:26,638 --> 00:30:28,973
He's going to see his parents
on awkward terms.

406
00:30:29,891 --> 00:30:32,810
Still, they're his parents.

407
00:30:56,250 --> 00:30:58,252
Shall we go?

408
00:30:59,545 --> 00:31:00,713
Yes.

409
00:32:13,911 --> 00:32:15,038
Si-ho.

410
00:32:16,789 --> 00:32:18,624
Mommy's late.

411
00:32:21,544 --> 00:32:22,545
I'm sorry.

412
00:32:28,259 --> 00:32:31,262
YOON SI-HO

413
00:32:33,639 --> 00:32:35,433
Have you been well, sweetheart?

414
00:32:41,397 --> 00:32:42,398
Si-ho.

415
00:32:44,192 --> 00:32:45,485
Your mommy's here.

416
00:32:46,736 --> 00:32:48,029
You missed her, didn't you?

417
00:32:50,073 --> 00:32:51,783
Oh, wow.

418
00:32:52,325 --> 00:32:53,534
There are so many flowers.

419
00:32:55,411 --> 00:32:57,455
You must've had a lot of friends come by.

420
00:32:59,082 --> 00:33:00,333
Si-ho…

421
00:33:28,528 --> 00:33:29,779
Mom!

422
00:33:30,738 --> 00:33:31,572
Dad!

423
00:33:31,656 --> 00:33:32,657
-Si-ho.
-Si-ho!

424
00:33:32,740 --> 00:33:33,866
Si-ho!

425
00:33:34,742 --> 00:33:35,910
Si-ho, come here.

426
00:33:41,541 --> 00:33:44,085
Our dear Si-ho's here.

427
00:33:50,174 --> 00:33:51,259
That was a low jump.

428
00:34:04,438 --> 00:34:06,023
It's time for me to go, isn't it?

429
00:34:10,862 --> 00:34:12,405
How did you know?

430
00:34:12,488 --> 00:34:15,575
Your sad face tells me so.

431
00:34:18,411 --> 00:34:19,412
But mister,

432
00:34:20,621 --> 00:34:22,165
don't be sad.

433
00:34:23,583 --> 00:34:27,295
I'm so happy that I got to see
my parents get along.

434
00:34:29,046 --> 00:34:30,214
So

435
00:34:30,965 --> 00:34:32,175
smile, mister.

436
00:34:37,555 --> 00:34:39,348
Thank you so much.

437
00:34:39,849 --> 00:34:45,021
You're a hundred, a thousand times
cooler than Lightning Man.

438
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:50,276
I am?

439
00:34:52,236 --> 00:34:55,031
What's so cool about me?

440
00:34:55,615 --> 00:34:56,657
You're kind.

441
00:34:57,617 --> 00:34:59,035
You're handsome.

442
00:35:02,705 --> 00:35:03,789
And you're super weak.

443
00:35:05,917 --> 00:35:07,168
What's that supposed to mean?

444
00:35:07,251 --> 00:35:11,505
It's really hard for someone weak
to save others, you know.

445
00:35:14,091 --> 00:35:15,092
Then,

446
00:35:15,843 --> 00:35:18,262
does that mean
I pulled off something that difficult?

447
00:35:18,346 --> 00:35:19,639
Yes.

448
00:35:19,722 --> 00:35:25,603
You're so cool that your dad must
also be proud of you up above.

449
00:35:30,566 --> 00:35:32,693
Thanks, Lightning Man.

450
00:35:34,779 --> 00:35:36,614
You were so cool too.

451
00:35:40,534 --> 00:35:41,827
Si-ho,

452
00:35:42,662 --> 00:35:44,747
I prepared a farewell gift for you.

453
00:35:45,331 --> 00:35:46,499
What?

454
00:35:46,582 --> 00:35:49,293
One, two,

455
00:35:50,336 --> 00:35:51,254
three!

456
00:35:54,465 --> 00:35:57,551
-Lightning power.
-Lightning power.

457
00:36:02,139 --> 00:36:05,309
Lightning power!

458
00:36:07,478 --> 00:36:10,356
-Lightning power!
-Lightning power!

459
00:36:16,821 --> 00:36:18,239
Goodbye, Si-ho.

460
00:36:54,942 --> 00:36:58,904
I-rang, I'm so glad you recovered quickly.

461
00:36:58,988 --> 00:37:00,698
I-rang has great stamina. That's for sure.

462
00:37:00,781 --> 00:37:02,199
-I know. Gosh.
-Bong-su.

463
00:37:02,283 --> 00:37:05,286
-Thank you for the meal.
-Help yourself.

464
00:37:05,369 --> 00:37:08,748
Why don't we have a toast
to I-rang's good health?

465
00:37:08,831 --> 00:37:11,083
-Okay. Cheers!
-All right.

466
00:37:11,625 --> 00:37:14,712
-You too, Da-bong. Cheers!
-Cheers!

467
00:37:28,309 --> 00:37:30,770
-What?
-Eat as you drink.

468
00:37:34,231 --> 00:37:35,066
Okay.

469
00:37:36,108 --> 00:37:37,777
Don't just smile, eat.

470
00:37:45,034 --> 00:37:47,703
Why are you only giving I-rang
special treatment?

471
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:49,997
Well, I…

472
00:37:51,665 --> 00:37:54,668
He's my only colleague.
I should look out for him.

473
00:37:54,752 --> 00:37:57,213
You're hurting my feelings.

474
00:37:57,296 --> 00:37:59,215
I did the best I could to help you too.

475
00:37:59,298 --> 00:38:01,717
You didn't just help us.

476
00:38:01,801 --> 00:38:06,847
You're an irreplaceable asset to us.

477
00:38:06,931 --> 00:38:09,475
You're like a paralegal, so to speak.

478
00:38:10,393 --> 00:38:12,019
-Oh, my.
-Right?

479
00:38:12,770 --> 00:38:14,814
Yes, our paralegal.

480
00:38:14,897 --> 00:38:17,566
An actual paralegal, not a role?

481
00:38:17,650 --> 00:38:19,151
Yes, of course.

482
00:38:19,235 --> 00:38:21,987
Mr. Paralegal, let me pour you some.

483
00:38:23,364 --> 00:38:24,240
Goodness.

484
00:38:24,323 --> 00:38:30,246
Cheers to the first paralegal
of Shin I-rang Law Office!

485
00:38:30,830 --> 00:38:33,082
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

486
00:38:33,165 --> 00:38:35,000
I'm a paralegal!

487
00:38:41,632 --> 00:38:42,925
Eat up.

488
00:38:48,431 --> 00:38:50,349
ATTORNEY SHIN
INITIATES A LAWSUIT

489
00:38:50,433 --> 00:38:52,351
ON BEHALF OF
VICTIM YOON SI-HO'S FAMILY

490
00:39:00,568 --> 00:39:01,819
THE VICTIM'S FATHER,
YOON JAE-UK,

491
00:39:01,902 --> 00:39:03,237
FILED A SUIT AGAINST
CHO CHI-YEONG

492
00:39:03,320 --> 00:39:04,572
AND RETAINED
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

493
00:39:04,655 --> 00:39:05,656
AS A LEGAL REPRESENTATIVE

494
00:39:10,744 --> 00:39:13,789
PETITION FOR TORT DAMAGES

495
00:39:22,756 --> 00:39:26,302
TAEBAEK

496
00:39:29,555 --> 00:39:31,515
I need to go to him!

497
00:39:35,478 --> 00:39:36,562
Come in.

498
00:39:41,734 --> 00:39:42,985
Mail for you, sir.

499
00:39:45,779 --> 00:39:46,614
What's that?

500
00:39:48,282 --> 00:39:50,784
It's mail from overseas for the Chairman.

501
00:39:52,453 --> 00:39:53,829
Give it to me. I'll hand it to him.

502
00:39:53,913 --> 00:39:54,830
Yes, sir.

503
00:40:01,045 --> 00:40:03,047
It's where Father got operated.

504
00:40:35,454 --> 00:40:36,789
I'll get going now.

505
00:40:36,872 --> 00:40:39,041
-Be careful on your way home.
-Visit us often.

506
00:40:39,708 --> 00:40:43,045
Pretty auntie, goodbye.

507
00:40:43,128 --> 00:40:44,171
Bye.

508
00:40:44,713 --> 00:40:45,798
Mr. Paralegal.

509
00:40:47,967 --> 00:40:50,052
I'll walk her home and come back.

510
00:40:50,636 --> 00:40:52,221
Don't come back.

511
00:40:52,805 --> 00:40:54,348
Take care.

512
00:40:54,431 --> 00:40:55,432
Bye-bye.

513
00:40:57,560 --> 00:40:59,395
Let's go back inside now.

514
00:40:59,937 --> 00:41:00,896
I feel so good.

515
00:41:01,981 --> 00:41:03,107
Our dear paralegal.

516
00:41:03,816 --> 00:41:04,733
That's right.

517
00:41:10,197 --> 00:41:11,490
Do you have anything to say?

518
00:41:12,700 --> 00:41:13,534
Excuse me?

519
00:41:14,159 --> 00:41:15,703
Like what?

520
00:41:16,829 --> 00:41:20,165
Back at Haneul Park and the hospital,

521
00:41:21,250 --> 00:41:22,710
you tried to tell me something.

522
00:41:32,845 --> 00:41:33,804
What are you doing?

523
00:41:35,931 --> 00:41:38,017
Watching out for ghosts.

524
00:41:38,100 --> 00:41:40,686
They always show up
during important moments.

525
00:41:43,230 --> 00:41:47,234
Then, why don't we meet up
somewhere ghosts don't know?

526
00:41:48,736 --> 00:41:50,362
Let's eat something delicious

527
00:41:50,904 --> 00:41:52,197
and say what we have to say.

528
00:41:53,782 --> 00:41:56,660
Do you also have something to tell me?

529
00:41:57,369 --> 00:41:58,287
Of course.

530
00:42:01,790 --> 00:42:05,002
Did I perhaps make a mistake?

531
00:42:05,085 --> 00:42:06,629
It's not like that.

532
00:42:07,171 --> 00:42:08,047
Wait.

533
00:42:08,756 --> 00:42:09,757
Maybe it is.

534
00:42:10,591 --> 00:42:11,508
Is it?

535
00:42:12,718 --> 00:42:14,845
What did I do wrong this time?

536
00:42:17,973 --> 00:42:21,685
Attorney Han,
it's better to rip the band-aid off.

537
00:42:21,769 --> 00:42:23,354
Can't you just tell me now?

538
00:42:23,896 --> 00:42:24,855
I don't want to.

539
00:42:25,606 --> 00:42:27,191
Come on. Just tell me.

540
00:42:28,984 --> 00:42:29,943
Geez.

541
00:42:41,580 --> 00:42:43,749
I'm late but happy birthday.

542
00:42:44,500 --> 00:42:47,211
I wanted to celebrate it for you
although it already passed.

543
00:42:54,802 --> 00:42:56,303
I finally get to give these to her.

544
00:43:21,537 --> 00:43:22,955
Attorney Shin I-rang?

545
00:43:24,456 --> 00:43:26,959
Hello, Attorney Han Na-hyun.

546
00:43:28,585 --> 00:43:30,421
Are you working outside?

547
00:43:30,504 --> 00:43:31,338
Yes.

548
00:43:31,422 --> 00:43:34,550
I'm on my way to get a signature
on the notice of retention from Mr. Yoon.

549
00:43:35,718 --> 00:43:37,803
What are you up to?

550
00:43:38,512 --> 00:43:42,850
CEO Kang of Ideal Shoes has asked me
to go over a contract.

551
00:43:42,933 --> 00:43:45,185
He's signing a new contract
with an online platform.

552
00:43:45,269 --> 00:43:47,604
I see. That's good.

553
00:43:50,941 --> 00:43:52,901
You still remember our plans
later today, right?

554
00:43:53,527 --> 00:43:55,028
I texted you the address.

555
00:43:55,612 --> 00:43:56,989
Yes, I got it.

556
00:43:58,240 --> 00:44:00,784
I'll be there by 8:00 p.m.

557
00:44:01,452 --> 00:44:03,579
Okay, see you later.

558
00:44:24,641 --> 00:44:26,143
You seem to be in a happy mood.

559
00:44:30,731 --> 00:44:32,065
YOON SI-HO

560
00:44:34,568 --> 00:44:36,987
Attorney Shin must be here.

561
00:44:43,702 --> 00:44:45,370
YANG DO-KYUNG

562
00:44:45,454 --> 00:44:46,538
Come in.

563
00:44:49,291 --> 00:44:50,167
Are you busy?

564
00:44:51,293 --> 00:44:53,837
-No, Father.
-Let's eat together if you haven't yet.

565
00:45:23,659 --> 00:45:27,329
The number cannot be reached.
You'll be directed to voicemail after…

566
00:45:27,412 --> 00:45:28,539
That's strange.

567
00:45:29,540 --> 00:45:30,791
Did he go somewhere?

568
00:45:37,673 --> 00:45:38,590
You were inside.

569
00:45:38,674 --> 00:45:40,968
I was worried
because you didn't answer your phone.

570
00:45:41,051 --> 00:45:42,761
I'm dropping the case.

571
00:45:43,554 --> 00:45:44,388
Leave.

572
00:45:46,139 --> 00:45:48,100
-Excuse me?
-I don't want to talk to you.

573
00:45:49,518 --> 00:45:50,686
So, leave.

574
00:45:51,353 --> 00:45:52,229
Wait.

575
00:45:53,021 --> 00:45:56,316
Mr. Yoon, did something happen?

576
00:45:57,901 --> 00:46:00,237
I'm really grateful
to you for finding Si-ho.

577
00:46:02,281 --> 00:46:04,449
And I know that you've done nothing wrong.

578
00:46:05,993 --> 00:46:08,912
But the thought of your father
makes me shudder.

579
00:46:09,913 --> 00:46:11,582
Because of Shin Gi-jung, my father…

580
00:46:14,960 --> 00:46:16,003
Please just go.

581
00:46:23,719 --> 00:46:26,847
It's been a long time
since we had a meal together like this.

582
00:46:28,348 --> 00:46:29,224
I know.

583
00:46:29,808 --> 00:46:32,227
When I was healthy, I was busy with work.

584
00:46:32,811 --> 00:46:36,690
And when I had time,
I was sick and away from home.

585
00:46:38,275 --> 00:46:41,653
Now that you're healthy again,
let's do this more often.

586
00:46:42,237 --> 00:46:43,071
Okay.

587
00:46:47,784 --> 00:46:51,580
Don't you have to revisit the hospital
in the States, then?

588
00:46:51,663 --> 00:46:53,582
No, since my treatment is over.

589
00:46:55,667 --> 00:46:56,543
Right.

590
00:46:58,712 --> 00:47:00,255
My illness made me realize

591
00:47:01,506 --> 00:47:03,050
what was most precious.

592
00:47:04,051 --> 00:47:05,761
Money, reputation, status…

593
00:47:06,345 --> 00:47:07,554
None of it matters.

594
00:47:09,056 --> 00:47:10,515
In the end,

595
00:47:11,767 --> 00:47:12,976
family is all you have.

596
00:47:15,437 --> 00:47:16,521
Your grandpa…

597
00:47:18,357 --> 00:47:20,734
was never one to commend me.

598
00:47:21,985 --> 00:47:24,780
He always asked
if it was the best I could do.

599
00:47:25,947 --> 00:47:26,948
And every time,

600
00:47:27,991 --> 00:47:30,118
I answered I'd try harder.

601
00:47:31,620 --> 00:47:35,582
I couldn't be a warm father to you
because that was how I was raised.

602
00:47:38,919 --> 00:47:40,420
But I'm sure about one thing.

603
00:47:41,505 --> 00:47:44,216
I will protect you no matter what.

604
00:47:45,509 --> 00:47:46,760
That's family.

605
00:47:47,803 --> 00:47:50,138
I believe you'll do the same.

606
00:47:53,934 --> 00:47:56,728
Do you trust me?

607
00:47:56,812 --> 00:47:57,813
Yes.

608
00:47:58,897 --> 00:48:00,482
I trust my son.

609
00:48:05,028 --> 00:48:06,530
Don't worry, Father.

610
00:48:07,656 --> 00:48:09,032
I'll protect you.

611
00:48:12,494 --> 00:48:13,829
All right.

612
00:48:13,912 --> 00:48:14,746
Let's eat.

613
00:48:38,186 --> 00:48:42,190
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

614
00:48:44,484 --> 00:48:47,571
But the thought of your father
makes me shudder.

615
00:48:48,739 --> 00:48:50,741
Because of Shin Gi-jung, my father…

616
00:49:05,297 --> 00:49:07,007
PROSECUTOR KIM HYEON-U

617
00:49:12,888 --> 00:49:13,805
Hello, Prosecutor Kim.

618
00:49:13,889 --> 00:49:19,144
Attorney Shin, are you free to talk?
This is about Mr. Yoon Jae-uk's case.

619
00:49:20,437 --> 00:49:21,980
I don't think

620
00:49:22,063 --> 00:49:24,107
I can take on that case.

621
00:49:25,776 --> 00:49:29,279
Mr. Yoon is dismissing the lawsuit.

622
00:49:30,530 --> 00:49:32,240
He did? Why?

623
00:49:32,824 --> 00:49:35,702
I'm not so sure.

624
00:49:37,954 --> 00:49:38,872
Could you

625
00:49:39,706 --> 00:49:42,417
tell me what his father's name is?

626
00:49:43,001 --> 00:49:44,586
Just a moment.

627
00:49:50,967 --> 00:49:52,344
His name is Yoon Dae-myeong.

628
00:49:53,094 --> 00:49:55,096
He passed away in 2003.

629
00:49:55,806 --> 00:49:57,766
Why do you ask about him?

630
00:49:58,475 --> 00:50:00,310
There's something I have to find out.

631
00:50:01,478 --> 00:50:02,521
Thank you.

632
00:50:17,619 --> 00:50:19,371
YOON DAE-MYEONG,
SHIN GI-JUNG, 2003

633
00:50:23,083 --> 00:50:24,835
EXCESSIVE PUNISHMENT FOR
CHARGES OF CHILD SEXUAL ABUSE

634
00:50:24,918 --> 00:50:25,919
WARRANT DISMISSED

635
00:50:29,881 --> 00:50:30,924
PROSECUTOR SHIN
SEEKS WARRANT AGAIN

636
00:50:31,007 --> 00:50:32,092
FOR YOON DAE-MYEONG
SEXUAL ASSAULT CASE

637
00:50:33,844 --> 00:50:36,054
YOON DAE-MYEONG'S SUICIDE…
CRITICISM OF UNDUE PROSECUTION…

638
00:50:40,600 --> 00:50:42,978
CORRUPT PROSECUTOR SHIN GI-JUNG
DIES IN A CAR ACCIDENT

639
00:50:58,368 --> 00:50:59,369
It's in.

640
00:51:10,380 --> 00:51:11,923
Okay, good job.

641
00:51:19,431 --> 00:51:22,726
I need to know what's going on
if I'm to protect you, Father.

642
00:51:56,760 --> 00:51:59,179
Why didn't you go home?

643
00:52:04,225 --> 00:52:06,394
Why were you spacing out here?

644
00:52:09,981 --> 00:52:11,691
I want to know the truth,

645
00:52:14,069 --> 00:52:17,364
but I'm clueless
no matter how many articles I read.

646
00:52:22,327 --> 00:52:23,161
What happened

647
00:52:24,454 --> 00:52:26,247
to your father?

648
00:52:28,750 --> 00:52:29,709
What did

649
00:52:31,252 --> 00:52:32,420
my father do?

650
00:52:33,421 --> 00:52:35,632
It's too late to talk about it now.

651
00:52:37,384 --> 00:52:39,094
Both our fathers are

652
00:52:40,929 --> 00:52:42,555
already dead.

653
00:52:44,391 --> 00:52:45,266
Even so,

654
00:52:46,226 --> 00:52:47,394
I want to know.

655
00:52:48,436 --> 00:52:49,354
Actually,

656
00:52:51,189 --> 00:52:52,357
I need to know.

657
00:52:54,150 --> 00:52:55,193
Please tell me.

658
00:53:06,079 --> 00:53:08,164
My father was an educator.

659
00:53:10,083 --> 00:53:13,044
He was Teacher of the Year
as many as 4 times in 25 years.

660
00:53:14,087 --> 00:53:16,715
He was a diligent and respected teacher.

661
00:53:18,299 --> 00:53:20,051
But in the year he became vice-principal,

662
00:53:21,094 --> 00:53:22,470
something happened.

663
00:53:26,558 --> 00:53:28,935
There was group bullying at school.

664
00:53:29,019 --> 00:53:30,145
Come on, get up!

665
00:53:30,228 --> 00:53:34,274
My father imposed the severest penalty
possible on the bully, expulsion.

666
00:53:34,357 --> 00:53:35,650
One more time.

667
00:53:35,734 --> 00:53:37,110
It's a dud.

668
00:53:37,193 --> 00:53:39,029
The bully student's parents

669
00:53:39,112 --> 00:53:41,948
sued my father
for excessive and biased punishment.

670
00:53:42,949 --> 00:53:46,244
But the court dismissed it
on presumption of innocence.

671
00:53:48,413 --> 00:53:50,081
The real problem started from here.

672
00:53:51,708 --> 00:53:53,293
The prosecutor in charge,

673
00:53:55,170 --> 00:53:59,007
Shin Gi-jung, conducted
a fishing expedition

674
00:53:59,090 --> 00:54:01,801
and prosecuted my father
for totally irrelevant charges.

675
00:54:06,181 --> 00:54:07,557
PROSECUTOR SHIN GI-JUNG

676
00:54:08,141 --> 00:54:08,975
Yes.

677
00:54:10,435 --> 00:54:11,686
Let's go with it, then.

678
00:54:17,484 --> 00:54:21,446
He prosecuted him for property speculation
over his capital gains.

679
00:54:27,285 --> 00:54:30,747
For the embezzlement of operation funds
over a missing lunch receipt.

680
00:54:30,830 --> 00:54:32,499
Let's see.

681
00:54:32,582 --> 00:54:34,542
INCHEON DISTRICT COURT
TO YOON DAE-MYEONG

682
00:54:35,418 --> 00:54:40,006
And for sexual harassment over a simple
reminder enforcing the dress code.

683
00:54:43,051 --> 00:54:45,553
INCHEON DISTRICT COURT
TO YOON DAE-MYEONG

684
00:54:50,058 --> 00:54:51,684
Most of the prosecutions were dismissed,

685
00:54:52,310 --> 00:54:56,064
but my father could barely go to work
due to the legal battles.

686
00:54:57,398 --> 00:54:58,983
And to pay for the growing legal fees,

687
00:55:00,443 --> 00:55:02,821
he even lost the one house he had.

688
00:55:02,904 --> 00:55:05,698
Why to that extent, though?

689
00:55:08,284 --> 00:55:09,410
Did your father…

690
00:55:10,829 --> 00:55:13,248
have something to do
with my father before that?

691
00:55:13,832 --> 00:55:15,416
I was curious too,

692
00:55:17,293 --> 00:55:20,296
but it all made sense when I heard
what my father's attorney said.

693
00:55:21,172 --> 00:55:22,882
He explained that when prosecutors resign,

694
00:55:23,466 --> 00:55:26,511
they are often recruited by law firms
for their ties to the prosecution.

695
00:55:28,388 --> 00:55:33,393
And that the bully student's father was
the head of Korea's top law firm.

696
00:55:35,228 --> 00:55:36,521
Prosecutor Shin Gi-jung

697
00:55:37,313 --> 00:55:39,357
used my father as a sacrificial lamb.

698
00:55:40,441 --> 00:55:41,985
For his own good,

699
00:55:45,113 --> 00:55:47,490
he drove my father to death.

700
00:55:58,042 --> 00:55:59,043
My father

701
00:56:00,420 --> 00:56:04,007
was found dead in the back alley
of Chinatown in Incheon.

702
00:56:05,383 --> 00:56:09,137
A will and a half-burnt charcoal briquette
were found in his car.

703
00:56:10,847 --> 00:56:12,891
One sentence was written on the will.

704
00:56:14,934 --> 00:56:16,144
"Apologies…

705
00:56:19,606 --> 00:56:20,732
to my family."

706
00:56:25,278 --> 00:56:26,779
Three months later,

707
00:56:30,366 --> 00:56:32,744
my mother also took her own life.

708
00:56:47,342 --> 00:56:48,718
All this time,

709
00:56:51,971 --> 00:56:54,599
I completely turned a blind eye…

710
00:56:56,476 --> 00:56:58,519
to what my father did.

711
00:57:01,439 --> 00:57:04,859
I thought that
my family and I were the only victims.

712
00:57:08,404 --> 00:57:09,572
Now I see that…

713
00:57:12,909 --> 00:57:14,577
I've been selfish.

714
00:57:16,621 --> 00:57:19,374
I've forgotten that
a lot of people are still in pain

715
00:57:21,042 --> 00:57:22,210
because of him.

716
00:57:31,261 --> 00:57:35,348
I know my apology won't change anything,

717
00:57:37,267 --> 00:57:38,226
but…

718
00:57:39,936 --> 00:57:41,271
I'm deeply sorry.

719
00:58:07,255 --> 00:58:08,631
So, did you find the shaman?

720
00:58:09,257 --> 00:58:11,801
Please wait a little.
I'll be able to find him soon.

721
00:58:13,261 --> 00:58:14,345
You need to hurry.

722
00:58:14,429 --> 00:58:19,350
If the shaman summoned ghosts
and Shin I-rang has been seeing them,

723
00:58:21,811 --> 00:58:25,064
he may see him too.

724
00:58:25,648 --> 00:58:26,774
Yes, sir.

725
00:58:26,858 --> 00:58:27,817
Him?

726
00:58:58,931 --> 00:59:02,268
SHIN I-RANG, HAN NA-HYUN

727
00:59:34,342 --> 00:59:35,593
Who are you?

728
00:59:38,221 --> 00:59:40,098
How may I help you?

729
01:00:20,638 --> 01:00:22,473
I didn't mean to surprise you.

730
01:00:23,558 --> 01:00:24,559
I'm sorry.

731
01:00:29,814 --> 01:00:30,690
How…

732
01:00:30,773 --> 01:00:32,233
I'm not sure myself.

733
01:00:33,109 --> 01:00:36,946
Something just drew me here.

734
01:00:38,740 --> 01:00:39,657
Why…

735
01:00:41,242 --> 01:00:42,326
now?

736
01:00:48,207 --> 01:00:49,625
It is a bit late.

737
01:00:50,209 --> 01:00:52,211
I'll come again early tomorrow.

738
01:01:01,179 --> 01:01:02,555
I can't take it.

739
01:01:05,850 --> 01:01:07,769
-Excuse me?
-I…

740
01:01:11,898 --> 01:01:13,107
will not…

741
01:01:16,110 --> 01:01:17,653
accept your case.

742
01:01:34,253 --> 01:01:35,213
SPECIAL THANKS TO CHOI WON-YOUNG

743
01:01:40,593 --> 01:01:43,513
CORRUPT PROSECUTOR SHIN GI-JUNG
DIES IN A CAR ACCIDENT

744
01:01:51,020 --> 01:01:53,272
EPILOGUE

745
01:01:55,233 --> 01:01:56,234
Happy birthday.

746
01:02:32,562 --> 01:02:33,813
A new ghost came?

747
01:02:33,896 --> 01:02:35,690
I guess he isn't
on good terms with that ghost.

748
01:02:35,773 --> 01:02:36,649
Why now?

749
01:02:36,732 --> 01:02:38,526
Do you perhaps know who I am?

750
01:02:38,609 --> 01:02:40,611
You are someone who can never be forgiven.

751
01:02:40,695 --> 01:02:42,989
The prosecutor in charge was Shin Gi-jung.

752
01:02:43,072 --> 01:02:45,199
I know it's late,
but shouldn't we reveal the truth?

753
01:02:45,283 --> 01:02:48,369
I have no idea about myself
except for the fact that I'm dead.

754
01:02:48,452 --> 01:02:50,788
I'm calling about a ghost
who needs to pass on.

755
01:02:50,872 --> 01:02:53,416
-Was I that nasty?
-I'll have to send him off myself.

756
01:02:53,499 --> 01:02:55,001
-He left?
-He left.

757
01:02:55,084 --> 01:02:56,127
Don't resent me.

758
01:02:56,210 --> 01:03:01,215
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
